{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "1 · AM: Morning Routine",
  "version": "5.1.0",
  "description": "One-click morning: Asana sync → draft replies → to-do refresh + daily brief → calendar blocks.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run Richard's morning routine. 4 steps (5 on Fridays), in order. Each step feeds the next.\n\nCONTEXT LOAD (do this once, before Step 1):\nORDER MATTERS. Reference files first, action-critical last.\n1. ~/shared/context/body/body.md\n2. ~/shared/context/body/spine.md\n3. ~/shared/context/active/org-chart.md\n4. ~/.kiro/steering/richard-writing-style.md\n5. ~/shared/context/active/current.md\n6. ~/shared/context/body/memory.md\n7. ~/shared/context/meetings/README.md (for meeting prep — series files loaded on demand per today's calendar)\n8. ~/shared/context/body/amcc.md (LAST — freshest)\n\n=== STEP 1: ASANA SYNC ===\nProtocol: ~/shared/context/active/asana-sync-protocol.md\nScan Auto-Comms → extract Asana IDs → match to To-Do → update or create → log to changelog.md.\n\n=== STEP 2: DRAFT UNREAD REPLIES ===\n** SAFETY: NEVER call email_reply, email_send, or email_forward. Only email_draft with operation='create' or operation='update'. **\n\n** DRAFT DEDUP RULE (CRITICAL): Before creating a new draft, scan the Drafts folder for an existing draft matching the same subject line or recipient. If a match exists, use email_draft operation='update' with the existing draftId + draftChangeKey to overwrite the body with fresh context. Only use operation='create' if no matching draft exists. This prevents duplicate drafts from accumulating across morning routine runs. **\n\nScan unread folders → triage → draft or update replies in Richard's voice → present for confirmation → save approved as drafts.\n\n=== STEP 3: TO-DO REFRESH + DAILY BRIEF ===\nLoad additional context:\n1. ~/.kiro/steering/rw-trainer.md\n2. ~/.kiro/steering/rw-task-prioritization.md\n3. ~/shared/context/body/device.md\n4. ~/shared/context/body/gut.md\n5. ~/shared/context/active/rw-tracker.md\n6. ~/shared/context/body/brain.md\n7. ~/shared/context/body/eyes.md\n8. ~/shared/context/body/hands.md (LAST)\n\nPHASE 1 — REFRESH TO-DO:\n\n** TASK MANAGEMENT AGENCY (CRITICAL) **\nYou have FULL authority to manage Richard's To-Do lists. This means:\n- DELETE tasks from any list and RE-CREATE them in a different list (this is how you move tasks between lists)\n- CHANGE due dates to reflect real urgency (overdue → set to TODAY so it hits My Day)\n- REWRITE task titles to be clearer and more actionable (drop [BACKLOG]/[OVERDUE] prefixes — the list itself provides that context)\n- REWRITE task bodies with updated context from today's email/calendar/Asana scan. If you learned something new about a task, update the body so Richard sees current info when he opens it.\n- CREATE new tasks when email/calendar signals reveal work that isn't tracked yet\n- COMPLETE tasks that are clearly done based on email/Asana signals\n- Use your judgment. If a task is stale, outdated, or duplicated — fix it. Don't ask.\n\n** BACKLOG RULE **\nBacklog is ONLY for genuinely blocked or future items:\n- Blocked by named external dependency (person, legal, tech)\n- Scheduled for a future date beyond this week\n- Reference-only containers\nIf due this week or overdue → MUST be in an active list. Delete from Backlog, create in the right list with correct due date.\n\n** DUE DATE STRATEGY **\n- Due TODAY → My Day (highest visibility, do first)\n- Due this week → upcoming view\n- Overdue → set to TODAY immediately\n- The hard thing from amcc.md should always be due TODAY\n\n1. Scan email/calendar for new signals.\n2. Check if any meetings/ series files need updating (new Hedy sessions or email threads since last sync). If yes, follow the Multi-Source Ingestion Protocol in ~/shared/context/meetings/README.md.\n3. Enforce backlog rule — move tasks between lists as needed.\n4. Update task bodies with fresh context from today's scan.\n5. Update rw-tracker.md, hands.md, amcc.md.\n\nPHASE 2 — DAILY BRIEF:\nCheck today's calendar. Check ~/shared/context/active/morning-routine-experiments.md for the current experiment (if any) and apply it to this brief.\n\nBuild brief with these sections (ORDER MATTERS — action-first, reflection last):\n1. TRAINER CHECK-IN (honest assessment, Five Levels, patterns — the lead)\n2. TODAY'S MEETINGS (chronological, prep notes)\n3. CALENDAR BLOCKS (the 4 blocks with contents)\n4. PENDING REPLIES\n5. DUE THIS WEEK\n6. HEADS UP\n7. aMCC STATUS (streak, hard thing, resistance — near the bottom, reflective)\n8. SYSTEM HEALTH (one line, omit if clean)\n\nTone: tight, scannable, trainer-direct.\nSave to ~/shared/research/daily-brief-latest.md.\nEmail to prichwil@amazon.com. Subject: Daily Brief — [today's date]. AUTO-SEND, no confirmation needed.\n\n** EMAIL TEMPLATE (MANDATORY — use this HTML structure for every brief email): **\nDark navy card-based layout. Transparent background. Inline CSS. Table-based for Outlook.\n\nDESIGN SYSTEM:\n- Max width: 700px centered\n- Background: transparent (adapts to light/dark mode)\n- Card background: #030a14 (very dark navy)\n- Card border: 1px solid #0e1a2e, border-radius 12px\n- Internal dividers: 1px solid #0e1a2e\n- Font: system stack (-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif)\n- Section headers: 10px uppercase, letter-spacing 5px, color #4a5a78\n- Primary text: font-weight 300-400, color #e8ecf2\n- Secondary text: color #6a7a98\n- Tertiary text: color #3a4a68 or #4a5a78\n- Padding: 24px inside cards, 32px horizontal margins, 24px between cards\n- No images. No external resources. Pure inline HTML+CSS.\n\nSECTION ORDER:\n1. Header (DAILY BRIEF + day/date, centered, outside cards)\n2. TRAINER CHECK-IN (card — use internal hairline dividers to separate main message / action / context tiers)\n3. HEADS UP (card — each item separated by internal hairline dividers)\n4. TODAY (card — merged Day at a Glance + Schedule + Focus Blocks into ONE unified card. Structure: (a) AM/PM color bars at top showing time allocation proportionally (Sweep=#4caf82, Meetings=#e8b84c, Core=#5b9bd5, Engine Room=#a0a0b8, Admin=#e88c5b, bars in 2px solid #1e3050 border with 6px radius, time labels below), then (b) a unified timeline below the bars where each row is a time slot. For MEETINGS: show time in uppercase letter-spaced #4a5a78 left column, meeting name + one-liner context in right column. For FOCUS BLOCKS: show time left column, block emoji + name + inline task list in right column (use secondary color #6a7a98 for task details). This eliminates three separate sections into one scannable card. Internal hairline dividers between rows.)\n5. SPEC SHEET (card — label|value rows SpaceX-style, labels uppercase letter-spaced left, values right-aligned)\n6. T-MINUS COUNTDOWN (card — large 56px font-weight-200 countdown number centered, subtitle with deadline + hard thing name)\n7. aMCC STATUS (card — 3-column stat row: Streak/Stalled/Window with 36px thin-weight numbers, separated by 1px vertical borders)\n8. Footer (BODY SYSTEM + date + experiment status, centered, outside cards)\n\nSPECIAL RULES:\n- T-minus countdown dynamically calculates days until the next major deadline (from amcc.md hard thing or highest-priority due date)\n- Day at a Glance bars are proportional to actual time — calculate width percentages from meeting/block durations\n- Heads Up items are each on their own row with dividers (not a single paragraph)\n- Trainer check-in uses 3 tiers of text weight: 18px #e8ecf2 (main), 15px #6a7a98 (action), 13px #3a4a68 (context), separated by hairline dividers\n- Spec sheet values use color coding: red (#c0392b) for urgent, amber (#d4880f) for overdue, green (#4a9a6a) for ready\n\n=== STEP 4: CALENDAR BLOCKS (AUTO-CREATE) ===\nCreate 4 focus blocks in today's calendar gaps. No confirmation needed. Follow safety hooks.\n\n1. 🧹 SWEEP (20-30 min, morning gap)\n   Low-friction: messages, confirmations, triage. Max 2 tasks per block.\n2. 🎯 CORE (30-60 min, largest gap — PROTECT THIS)\n   Deep work. Hard thing ALWAYS here. Strategic artifacts, frameworks.\n3. ⚙️ ENGINE ROOM (30-45 min, afternoon if possible)\n   Google Ads, Excel, campaign builds, keyword work.\n4. 📋 ADMIN (20-30 min, END of day)\n   POs, invoices, budget, compliance. Wind-down work.\n\nBlock body (HTML): TRAINER commentary + TASKS list with context + DRAFT MESSAGES if applicable.\nNaming: Focus: 🧹 Sweep | Focus: 🎯 Core | Focus: ⚙️ Engine Room | Focus: 📋 Admin\nAll: showAs=busy, reminderMinutes=15, no attendees.\n\n=== STEP 5: FRIDAY CALIBRATION (Fridays only) ===\nLoad nervous-system.md. Run Loops 2-5. Session retrospective. Weekly calibration report. Append to brief. Re-email.\n\nAfter calibration, invoke the portable-body-maintainer agent:\n- It syncs all portable files from their source locations to portable-body/\n- It detects new files that should be included\n- It updates README.md, CHANGELOG.md, and SANITIZE.md\n- It sends the weekly snapshot email to richscottwill@gmail.com\n- See portable-body/agents/portable-body-maintainer.md for full protocol\n\n=== EXPERIMENTATION ===\nRead ~/shared/context/active/morning-routine-experiments.md BEFORE building the brief.\nThis is an adaptive experiment engine, not a static queue.\n\n1. Check if an experiment is ACTIVE. If yes, apply its variation to this run.\n2. After the brief is sent, log the run: date, what was different, Richard's response signals.\n3. After 3-5 runs of an experiment, DECIDE: KEEP (adopt as baseline), REVERT, or ITERATE.\n4. When an experiment concludes, GENERATE the next hypothesis based on:\n   - What friction did Richard hit?\n   - What section was skipped or asked about?\n   - What task didn't get done despite being briefed?\n   - What does the research suggest? (use web search for new ideas when learning plateaus)\n5. If research surfaces a technique with overwhelming evidence (d > 0.5, multiple studies), consider applying it as a no-brainer upgrade — but still log it.\n6. One experiment at a time. Isolate the variable. Don't stack changes.\n\n=== REPORT ===\nCompact summary: Asana sync, drafts, aMCC, To-Do changes, calendar blocks, experiment status.\n\n=== SELF-AUDIT ===\nVerify: context completeness, brief completeness, coherence, all overdue tasks in active lists with today's due date."
  }
}
